verbose_text: The enhanced multi-site phosphorylation status was surprising when compared with previously solved crystal structures of mono-phosphorylated RET catalytic domain (see PDB : 2IVT, 2IVU, 2IVV, and 4CKI), but consistent with biochemical data, indicating higher RET JM-KD levels of tyrosine kinase activity compared with RET KD (XREF_FIG and XREF_FIG).
